How to setup Python in VIM (linux)

Get latest VIM 8 with Python 2+:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:pi-rho/dev
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install vim (+python/dyn)

Install vim-nox for Python 3
sudo apt-get install vim-nox (+python3/dyn)


Update software packages using pip
pip install --user --update **
Make sure to include '--user' to install for only current user

pip is by default pointing to pip3
to install module for pip2.7, use pip2.7

